snippet.textDisplay:
Hey MatPat! I've got a good theory dive for you!

The new Pokemon games, each town has its own giant stadium for pokemon matches. Stadiums like that are huge expenses not just to build but also in operating costs. Plus, the team or league usually gets the town to put forward the costs for it, or threaten to take the franchise that town has elsewhere. It looks like this entire areas economy is based on the Pokemon league! Sounds like a recipe for failure to me.

snippet.textDisplay: I have a possible theory on this now, what if William Afton was a copy cat serial killer. And in the mini game where we see "pink guy" maybe he ISN'T Afton, but another original killer who was convicted. In the book Into the Pit, when the kid, Oswald, goes back and he's seeing that the kids are all laid out, we've seen that before! In the mini game with pink guy, when we walk through to see the 6 children laid out in the back room, that was the showing of the original 1985 location and the killer was smiling that's "pink guy" and he was arrested. So maybe pink guy really isn't William, maybe William is a copy cat.
